@* Size is a step on the shared TrackSize scale, the same one FlareProgress and FlareMeter use. The steps are
   labels, not measurements: each theme maps them onto its own track and handle tokens. Switch the theme to
   see it - MD3 Expressive ramps the track right up, while FluentUI2 deliberately draws one geometry at every
   step, so these five sliders are identical there. That is the theme's call to make, not the scale's. *@
<FlareStack Gap="FlareSpacing.Large" Style="max-width:30rem;">
    <FlareSlider @bind-Value="_v" Size="TrackSize.Xs" Label="XSmall (default)" />
    <FlareSlider @bind-Value="_v" Size="TrackSize.Sm" Label="Small" />
    <FlareSlider @bind-Value="_v" Size="TrackSize.Md" Label="Medium" />
    <FlareSlider @bind-Value="_v" Size="TrackSize.Lg" Label="Large" />
    <FlareSlider @bind-Value="_v" Size="TrackSize.Xl" Label="XLarge" />
</FlareStack>

@code {
    private double _v = 50;
}
